# Finio — environment variables template
#
# This is a TEMPLATE. It contains no real keys — it's safe to commit.
#
# To use the app:
#   1. Copy this file and rename it to: .env.local
#   2. Replace the placeholder values below with your real values
#   3. .env.local is gitignored, so your real keys stay on your machine
#
# Never put real keys in this file. Only .env.local.
#
# L1-1 (2026-05-28): VITE_ANTHROPIC_KEY removed. Anthropic now proxied via
# the Supabase Edge Function `ask-sonu-proxy`. The Anthropic key lives in
# Supabase Function secrets:
#   supabase secrets set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Any VITE_ANTHROPIC_KEY left in your local .env.local should be deleted —
# it's no longer read.
#
# L1-1b (2026-05-28): VITE_TRADING212_API_KEY removed. The Trading 212
# integration (fetchT212Portfolio / mapT212ToPortfolio) was dead code that
# bundled the API key into the client. Deleted. If T212 sync returns, it'll
# be a server-side proxy like ask-sonu-proxy.

# ── Supabase (required) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-SUPABASE-ANON-KEY

# ── Observability (optional — L1-4) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Activate by installing the SDKs:
#   npm i @sentry/react@^8 posthog-js@^1
# Then set the DSNs below. Empty values = SDKs no-op silently.
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=
VITE_POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.i.posthog.com
